22/07/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said on TGRT television that the military may invade northern Iraq. 
Speaking on Saturday (July 21st), he said the aim "is not to enter Iraq, but to neutralise the PKK (Kurdistan Workers' Party)". 
Turkey charges that PKK terrorists are using northern Iraq to stage attacks in Turkey. 
(AFP, Anadolu news agency, ANA MPA, Focus - 21/07/07; TurkishPress.com - 20/07/07)
